HEADWORD: Plesimorphism
<hw>Ple`si*mor"phism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ near
+ <grk>morfh`</grk> form.]</ety> <fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>The
property possessed by some substances of crystallizing in closely
similar forms while unlike in chemical composition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plesiomorphous</ent>⟦br⟧
